Serving our neighbors in need ğŸ™ğŸ»

With your help this coming week, Tatte is joining with DoorDash to serve our neighbors in need.
From December 13th to December 19th, for every Tatte order placed via our exclusive delivery partner DoorDash, $3 will be donated to organizations on the frontlines fighting hunger and food insecurity in our communities.

In Greater Boston: Project Bread @projectbread connects people and communities in Massachusetts to reliable sources of food while advocating for policies that make food more accessibleâ€”so that no one goes hungry

In DMV: The Capital Area Food Bank @capitalareafoodbank provides more than 50 million meals to almost half a million area residents, every year. Because food alone doesnâ€™t solve hunger, they also address the root causes of hunger through multiple education programs and innovative service delivery partnerships
The holiday season is a wonderful reminder of the gifts we have to share, especially when we can be of service to others. Our heartfelt thanks for giving back with us.

From all of us at Tatte and DoorDash teams. 

Keep reading to learn more about these amazing organizations! #givingback #holidays #projectbread #capitalonefoodbank #doordash #tattebakery

Today is the last day to join us in our effort to support the people of Ukraine â¤ï¸ 

In the small ways we can at Tatte, we want to continue supporting efforts providing frontline humanitarian care to the Ukrainian people. 

Starting tomorrow, March 9, and through March 15, we will be donating 100% of sales of our Flourless Plain Brownies in all cafes, Boston and DC and at Tatte at Home shipping nationwide. 
All sales will go directly to World Central Kitchen, www.wck.org and The Polish Humanitarian Action, www.pah.org.pl
who are on the ground providing meals, clothes, shelter, and other urgent needs to Ukrainians displaced by the ongoing war. 

We would like to thank Valrhona @valrhonausa @valrhonafrance for partnering with us and donating hundreds of kilos of chocolate for this important effort!! and to our bakery teams in Boston and DC who are hard at work baking many more brownies in support of this effort,
Thank you! ğŸ™ŒğŸ»ğŸ™ğŸ»â¤ï¸ğŸ« 
To our guests, we appreciate your partnership supporting this effort. Know that every plain brownie you purchase this week or ship to your loved ones will go directly to support this important effort.

Have you tried making our mushroom Galette yet ? As a kid during the winter season we used to go and pick mushrooms, it was an entire family kind of activity with all parents, grandparents and cousins. We made the most delicious stew from it adding potatoes, tomatoes, plenty of herbs and chicken stock. We each got a small amount as there was never enough. Until today itâ€™s one of my favorite childhood memory . I took my love for mushrooms and created this delicious Galette. You can make it with mushrooms, tomatoes, cheese, or make it sweet with pears, peaches or strawberries in season. Dust it with sea salt, Zaatar, Sesame or sanded sugar, make it your own. Recipe available @foodandwine March issue on newsstand or link in bio. I stopped by the pastry kitchen today to say hi to everyone. I even remember saying to everyone â€œplease let me just bake, Iâ€™m not the owner on the days Iâ€™m baking...â€ back then I desperately needed that quiet time in the kitchen to balance my life ... within 5min w/the finish team today I pulled my sleeves and start topping the cheesecakes with the team. it was fun and all I could wish is to stay there for the day.
